                     <interp inst="t18060917-51-person492" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . - A. I believe it is not.</p>
               <p>Q. The body of the draft, what do you think of that. - A. It is not his hand writing.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18060917-51-person493">
                  JOSEPH 
                  FEARN
               <interp inst="t18060917-51-person493" type="surname" value="FEARN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18060917-51-person493" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18060917-51-person493" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , JUN. sworn. Examined by Mr. Knapp. You are the son of Mr. 
               <persName id="t18060917-51-person494">
                  Samuel 
                  Fearn
               <interp inst="t18060917-51-person494" type="surname" value="Fearn"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18060917-51-person494" type="given" value="Samuel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18060917-51-person494" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . - A. Yes.</p>
               <p>Q. Are you acquainted with your father's hand writing. - A. Most assuredly.</p>
               <p>Q. Is that your father's hand writing, or not. - A. I believe it is not.</p>
               <p>Q. What do you think of the body. - A. Certainly not.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18060917-51-person495">
                  THOMAS 
                  AMOS
               <interp inst="t18060917-51-person495" type="surname" value="AMOS"></interp>
