                  </persName>
             sworn. Examined by Mr. Knapp. Q. Were you in Holborn at the time of the prisoner's apprehension. - A. I was coming along Holborn at the time Mr. Pattisal was crying out Stop him, I took him immediately and took him into the Seagoe coffee-house.</p>
               <p>(The draft read in court.)</p>
               <p>LYGSTH Th. 1806.</p>
               <p>Messrs. Bond and Co. pay to J. Williams, Esq. One Hundred and Fifty Pounds.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18060917-51-person496">
                  SAMUEL 
                  FEARN
               <interp inst="t18060917-51-person496" type="surname" value="FEARN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18060917-51-person496" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
